headline: DECK Q1 Earnings Call: Sales Miss Expectations, Margin Expansion and Cautious Outlook
summary: Footwear and apparel conglomerate Deckers (NYSE:DECK) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 6.5% year on year to $1.02 billion. Its GAAP EPS of $1 per share was 66.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
